    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Crush your <strong>cardamom pods</strong> open by squashing them with the side of a knife</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[450ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [600ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Heat a pot with a matching lid, with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-basa-sultana-rice-and-indian-style-carrot-slaw/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add your <strong>ground turmeric </strong>and<strong> crushed cardamom pods</strong> to the pot and cook for 20 secs or until fragrant, then add your <strong>basmati rice</strong>, <strong>sultanas </strong>and<strong> vegetable stock </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked \u2013 this is your <strong>sultana rice</strong></p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-basa-sultana-rice-and-indian-style-carrot-slaw/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, top, tail, peel and grate your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Cut your<strong> lemon[s] </strong>into wedges</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander </strong>finely, including the stalks</p><p>Strip your<strong> mint leaves </strong>from their stems and chop them finely, discarding the stems</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-basa-sultana-rice-and-indian-style-carrot-slaw/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Roughly chop your<strong> cherry tomatoes</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped cherry tomatoes</strong>, 1/3 of the <strong>chopped mint</strong> and 1/3 of the <strong>chopped coriander</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) to a bowl with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and mix it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato salsa</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-basa-sultana-rice-and-indian-style-carrot-slaw/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basa fillet[s] </strong>to a bowl with your <strong>curry powder </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up until fully coated<strong> </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> coated basa</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-basa-sultana-rice-and-indian-style-carrot-slaw/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated basa</strong> and cook for 3-4 min on each side or until cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>curried basa</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-basa-sultana-rice-and-indian-style-carrot-slaw/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the fish is cooking, add the <strong>grated carrot</strong>, <strong>sliced spring onion</strong>,<strong> nigella seeds</strong>,<strong> remaining chopped mint </strong>and <strong>remaining chopped coriander </strong>to a bowl</p><p>Add the juice of <strong>half</strong> the<strong> lemon[s]</strong>,<strong> </strong>2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]<strong> </strong></span><strong>olive oil </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and mix it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>Indian-style carrot slaw</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-basa-sultana-rice-and-indian-style-carrot-slaw/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> curried basa</strong> over the <strong>sultana rice</strong> with the <strong>Indian-style carrot slaw</strong> to the side</p><p>Top the fish with the<strong> tomato salsa </strong>and garnish with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lemon wedges</strong></p><p>Tip: Watch out for the cardamom pods!</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
